project layout: https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/1.1.x/tutorial/layout/




run flask

~/dev/project/python/tesorio-scraper$ export FLASK_APP=flaskr/api.py
~/dev/project/python/tesorio-scraper$ export FLASK_ENV=development
~/dev/project/python/tesorio-scraper$ flask run
$ python3 -m flask run -> This should work!!!
$ pipenv run api



$ export FLASK_APP=flaskr
$ python3 -m flask init-db
---> comand from pipFile:
$ export FLASK_APP=flaskr
$ pipenv run init_db

Initialized the database.
There will now be a flaskr.sqlite file in the instance folder in your project.
It has executed the schema loading

run sqlitebrowser
$ sqlitebrowser

$sqlite
.quit -> exit
.open instance/flaskr.sqlite -> will open the database created





run unit test
$ pipenv run pytest




###### to run scripts from pipFile
pipenv run batch
pipenv run tests





